        <div type="footnotes">
            <note xml:id="foot.f1">Boehm refers to CD’s daughter <ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_1225.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Henrietta Emma Litchfield</ref> and <ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_1311.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Albert Venn Dicey</ref>.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f2"><ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_6904.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Josef Daniel Böhm</ref>.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f3"><ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_6889.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Georgina Boehm</ref>.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f4">Josephine and <ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_6887.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Florence Boehm</ref>.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f5"><ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_6882.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Edgar Collins Boehm</ref>.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f6"><ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_6900.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Fanny Boehm</ref>.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f7">Boehm’s grandfather’s brother has not been identified.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f8"><hi rend="italic">Schindeldach</hi>: shingle roof (German).</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f9">Leutschau was a town in the German-speaking Zipser region of the Kingdom of Hungary (now Levoča in eastern Slovakia).</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f10">CD discussed the inheritance of habitual gestures in <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_2400.xml" resp="#mjhawkins"><hi rend="italic">Expression</hi></ref> pp. 33–4 and n. 8.</note>
